# ===== DATABRICKS WORKSPACE & CLI ARTIFACTS =====
# These directories/files are created by the Databricks CLI on the local machine
# during `databricks auth login`, `databricks bundle deploy`, etc.
# They contain auth tokens, bundle state, and workspace caches — never commit.
.databricks/
.databrickscfg
.bundle/
.databricks-cli/

# ===== GCP CREDENTIALS =====
# Service account JSON keys are the #1 leak vector for GCP projects.
# Excluding *.json wholesale; the !package*.json exception is for Node projects
# (irrelevant here, but kept as a defensive default if the repo ever grows).
*.json
!package.json
!package-lock.json

# ===== PYTHON =====
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.so
.Python
.venv/
venv/
env/
.env
*.env
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/

# ===== JUPYTER / NOTEBOOK OUTPUTS =====
.ipynb_checkpoints/
*.ipynb_checkpoints/

# ===== IDE / EDITOR =====
.vscode/settings.json
.vscode/launch.json
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# ===== DATA (raw CSVs, parquet, downloaded archives) =====
# The Olist CSVs live in GCS, not in the repo. data/README.md will document
# how to download them from Kaggle. The data files themselves stay out.
data/*.csv
data/*.parquet
data/*.zip
data/*.tar.gz
!data/README.md

# ===== OS METADATA =====
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini

# ===== LOGS =====
*.log
logs/
